  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a  user, I want to send ETH so that I do not pay high Gas price and I do not need to adjust it manually each time\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Currently, Gas price is hardcoded to 21 Gwei. We need to adjust it and use lowest Standard price of mainnet.  There is a JSON-RPC method to get the current gas price https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_gasprice that can be used\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nGas price is adjusted to match current lowest Standard price\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nGas price is hardcoded and is always 21 Gwei, so user need to go to wallet and manually adjust it for each transaction. \r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet\r\n- Send Transaction\r\n- Open Advanced\r\n- Tap on field with fee\r\n-On Transaction Fee screen check Gas Price\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.13 and develop build \r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
